WHY 200M BUFFER?
Typical walking distance to/from stop.
Captures immediate stop environment.
GEOMETRY TYPES:
â€¢ Sidewalks = LINESTRING (path)
â€¢ Stops = POINT (location)
â€¢ Buffer = POLYGON (200m circle)
ST_INTERSECTION handles partial
segment overlaps correctly.
INTERPRETATION:
â€¢ High score: Dense sidewalk network
â€¢ Low score: Sparse infrastructure
USE CASES:
â€¢ First/last-mile analysis
â€¢ ADA compliance planning
â€¢ Identify walkability gaps
LIMITATIONS:
â€¢ Doesn't assess condition/quality
â€¢ Doesn't include crosswalks
â€¢ Length is proxy for access
